cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DL, cs.IR 

The paper involves the development of a fracture classification system using automated measurements from longitudinal studies. This involves the use of quantitative morphologic and bone density determinants, which are computed and classified using a committee of support vector machines. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), deep learning (cs.DL), and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
